<TITLE> CA sits with top bureaucrats next Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 13 (bdnews24.com)  Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed will meet with the secretaries of all ministries and departments on Aug 18 ahead of the upazila polls, an official said Wednesday. Kazi Md Aminul Islam, secretary of the Chief Adviser's Office, gave bdnews24.com the date of the meeting but could not say anything about the meeting's agenda. An official of the cabinet division, preferring anonymity, said the CA would discuss the role of field level government officials during the national polls and upazila polls. Progress of various development projects implementation, disaster management and food situation in the country would also be on the agenda of the meeting, the official said. He added that the bureaucrats may raise the issue of extending their retirement age. It would be the fourth such meeting since Fakhruddin Ahmed took over as chief adviser on Jan 13 last year. bdnews24.c
